Package game

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Battleship
    Responsible for beginning the program and starting the GameController object
    Board
    Has a PlayerType, Width, Height, and array of board squares
    BoardSquare
    Has a PlayerType, a ship which can be null, and a boolean for whether or not it has been shot
    Computer
    Gets random values for taking a shot and placing a ship
    Coordinates
    Just has x and y coordinates
    GameController
    Runs the game.
    GameModel
    Contains the Human and Computer model classes that contain all model code for the game
    GameView
    Responsible for all printing to the console.
    Human
    The subclass of Player for Human Players
    Player
    Has a PlayerType, a Board, and an array of Ships: Carrier, Battleship, Cruiser, Submarine, or Destroyer
    Ship
    Has a type, an orientation, an x coordinate, a y coordinate, and a number of hits
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    PlayerType
    PlayerType--Can be human or computer
    ShipOrientation
    ShipOrientation--can be horizontal or vertical
    ShipType
    ShipType enum has name and length associated.
